        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏷️ HARMONIZED — 25pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">H(4)+A(1)+R(1)+M(3)+O(1)+N(1)+I(1)+Z(10)+E(1)+D(2) · Elegant and scoreable</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Attempt a 10-Letter Word</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Not every game offers a 10-letter opportunity. You need specific board conditions and rack tiles to align. Here's when to look for them.</p>

      <!-- Purple strategy tiles -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Open Boards:</span> A 10-letter word needs an open row or column with at least 10 consecutive squares available. Mid-game boards with parallel plays rarely offer this space.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Existing Stems:</span> When you see -IZE, -ATE, or -TION on the board, check if adding your rack tiles creates a valid 10-letter word. These endings are the most extendable.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Point Differential:</span> If you're behind by 40+ points, hunting for a 10-letter bingo is worth the risk. A 75-100 point play can flip any game.</p></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Insight callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">A 10-letter word spanning the entire center row hits <span class="text-white font-medium">two Triple Word Score squares</span>, potentially multiplying your base score by 9. This is how single plays exceed 200 points.</p>
      </div>

